lure mode. The bug only appears when real processing time, real I/O scheduling, real queue or buffer back-pressure, and real OS thread/process overhead interact under load. REAL-INFRA: Yes — actual wall-clock timing and real OS process/thread scheduling are required; mocking any component replaces real latency with zero-cost stubs and trivially passes. MOCK-HIDE: Any mock of a processing stage would hide the real bottleneck, causing the test to always pass regardless of actual throughput. LLM-DEP: None. MULTI-STEP: None. REJECTION-GATE: Integration was considered but rejected — in-process integration tests cannot reproduce realistic scheduling, I/O contention, or buffer back-pressure that cause entries to be dropped or delayed under a true 10 k eps burst.","test_description":"Launch the tool as a real subprocess. Drive it with a producer that emits 10,000 structured JSON log entries per second for at least 5 seconds (50,000 total). Measure end-to-end: assert that (a) all 50,000 entries appear in the output or acknowledged store, (b) the pipeline's reported lag/queue depth never exceeds a defined threshold (e.g., 1 second of backlog), and (c) no entries are silently dropped.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.13,"System":0.8,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9550,"cache_read_input_tokens":3199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9550},"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9db25e2a-2e07-4fc7-9bac-88313bc09b56","uuid":"c6af9826-c65d-44f3-af96-890317f4c476"}
